      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING KIMELI (2) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 2.25 lengths at Q Parklands in a handy 29.71 beating Miss Bear. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Will go close again if runs up to latest. SUNLIT AMBER (8) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (20.03) in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Bold showing expected. LAKODA TALK (1) was in the minors two back (20.06) at this track but ran below best last time there, finishing 7th. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Cannot be taken lightly. LOCO BLAZE (7) jumps at a shorter distance and still warrants respect.",
